data.title: Movies and TV Shows
data.meta_description: Casey Kasem's filmography, sorted by online popularity. Learn more about the television and films they've appeared in.
data.text:
Saturday Night Live

as Self - Cameo (uncredited) • 1 episode • # 46 most popular show

Saturday Night Live (SNL) is a live sketch comedy and variety show that has been a staple of American television since its debut in 1975. The show features a talented ensemble cast who perform a series of comedic sketches, musical performances, and celebrity impressions. SNL is known for its satirical commentary on current events and pop culture, often pushing the boundaries of social and political humor. With a new episode airing every Saturday night, SNL has become a cultural phenomenon and has launched the careers of numerous comedy legends.

ALF

as Himself • 1 episode • # 705 most popular show

ALF is an American sitcom focused on the misadventures of a sarcastic extraterrestrial named ALF, who becomes a permanent resident with the Tanner family after his spacecraft crashes on Earth. The show combines family dynamics with science fiction elements, exploring themes of friendship, culture clash, and the concept of family.

Looney Tunes: Back in Action

as Shaggy (voice) • # 3,173 most popular movie

Looney Tunes: Back in Action is a 2003 American live-action/animated comedy film that follows the adventures of Bugs Bunny and Daffy Duck as they team up with stuntman Damien Drake Jr. on a mission to find Damien's father and a missing blue diamond while evading the pursuit of the Acme Corp.

Rugrats in Paris: The Movie

as Wedding DJ (voice) • # 4,058 most popular movie

Rugrats in Paris: The Movie is a 2000 animated comedy film and the second installment based on the Nickelodeon animated television series Rugrats. The story follows the adventurous journey of a group of toddlers as they explore Paris, learning important life lessons along the way.

Scooby-Doo and the Ghoul School

as Shaggy Rogers / Mirror Monster (voice) • # 4,816 most popular movie

Scooby-Doo and the Ghoul School is a 1988 animated comedy horror made-for-television film featuring Scooby, Shaggy, and Scrappy-Doo as gym teachers at Miss Grimwood's Finishing School for Girls, which is actually a school for daughters of famous monsters.

Scooby-Doo! and the Reluctant Werewolf

as Shaggy Rogers (voice) • # 4,949 most popular movie

Scooby-Doo! and the Reluctant Werewolf is a 1988 animated comedy horror made-for-television film where Shaggy is transformed into a werewolf. With the help of Scooby, Scrappy, and Shaggy's girlfriend, they must compete in a spooky road race against other monsters to reverse the curse.

Scooby-Doo! and the Legend of the Vampire

as Shaggy (voice) • # 5,514 most popular movie

Scooby-Doo! and the Legend of the Vampire is a 2003 American direct-to-video animated adventure film, and the fifth in a series of direct-to-video films based on the Scooby-Doo Saturday morning cartoons. It features the iconic characters solving a mystery involving the Yowie Yahoo, who is kidnapping musicians at a concert in Vampire Rock, Australia.

Aloha Scooby-Doo!

as Shaggy (voice) • # 5,716 most popular movie

Aloha, Scooby-Doo! is a 2005 American animated adventure film and the eighth installment in a series of direct-to-video animated films based on the Scooby-Doo Saturday morning cartoons. It follows the Mystery Gang as they travel to Hawaii for the Big Kahuna of Hanahuna Surfing Contest and encounter the vengeful Wiki Tiki spirit and his demons.

Scooby-Doo! and the Monster of Mexico

as Shaggy (voice) • # 6,024 most popular movie

Scooby-Doo! and the Monster of Mexico is a 2003 American direct-to-video animated adventure film and the sixth in a series of direct-to-video films based on the Scooby-Doo Saturday morning cartoons. It follows the gang as they visit Veracruz, Mexico, at the invitation of Fred's friend Alejo Otero, only to encounter the legendary monster, El Chupacabra.

Scooby-Doo! in Where's My Mummy?

as Shaggy (voice) • # 6,131 most popular movie

Scooby-Doo! in Where's My Mummy? is a 2005 American animated adventure film and the ninth installment in a series of direct-to-video animated films based on the Scooby-Doo cartoons. The movie follows the Mystery Inc. gang as they encounter a supernatural mystery in Egypt.
